"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(*) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM superhero WHERE height_cm BETWEEN 150 AND 180)) AS percentage\nFROM \n    superhero\nJOIN \n    publisher ON superhero.publisher_id = publisher.id\nWHERE \n    height_cm BETWEEN 150 AND 180\n    AND publisher.publisher_name = 'Marvel Comics';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of superheroes with a height between 150 and 180 cm who are published by Marvel Comics. It uses a subquery to count the total number of superheroes within the specified height range and then calculates the percentage of those who are published by Marvel Comics."